Ethel Azama https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethel_Azama 0 Ethel Azama (August 28, 1934 – March 7, 1984) was an American jazz and popular singer and recording artist. She sang regularly in nightclubs and other concert venues between the mid-1950s and 1984. Ethel was born and raised in Honolulu, Hawaii and was of Okinawan ancestry. She was a Nisei or second-generation Japanese American. Ethel_Azama ( August_28_,_1934 – March_7_,_1984 ) was an_American_jazz and popular_singer_and_recording_artist .
